```js
image:"https://example.com/IMAGE.png",
footer:{text:"TEXT",icon_url:"{SERVER.ICON}"}
```
`embed help` for more information
`embed variables` to see list of variables
`embed colors` to see list of color variables

actions.message:
Create **Custom Embed** in **Discord**

This command allows you to create custom embed from json format 
here's a few step to do it if you're new to discord embed

Always use `" "` between the text if it's string/text
for an example you don't have to use it with color,timestamp,etc.

**Command**: `embed <embed>`

**Plaintext**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}pt:`
`plaintext:"TEXT"`

**Title**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}t:`
`title:"THE TITLE"`

**Description**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}d:`
`description:"THE DESCRIPTION"`

**Title + Description**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}t:,${tempVars("ap")}d:`
`title:"THE TITLE",description:"THE DESCRIPTION"`

**Title + URL**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}t:,${tempVars("ap")}u:`
`title:"THE TITLE",url:""https://example.com/"`
actions.name: Set Embed Description

actions.message:
**Author (Name)**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}a:{${tempVars("ap")}n:}`
`author:{name:"USERNAME"}`

**Author (Name + Icon + Url)** 
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}a:{${tempVars("ap")}n:,${tempVars("ap")}iu:,${tempVars("ap")}u:}`
`author:{name:"USERNAME",icon_url:"https://image.com/image.png",url:"https://example.net/"}`

If you wish to automatically use your name and your avatar you could
use built in **Variables** in **Embed Builder**, this is how it's done;
`author:{name:"{USER}",icon_url:"{USER.AVATAR}"}`


**SEE LIST OF AVAILABLE VARIABLES**
**Command:** `embed variable`

you can also use the built in **Embed Builder** variables title, description, thumbnail, etc.
actions.name: Set Embed Description

actions.message:
**Color**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}c:`
`color:#000000`

**Description + Color**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}d:,${tempVars("ap")}c:`
`description:"THE DESCRIPTION",color:#000000`

for **Color** you don't have to put `" "` between the input

**Color** is using **decimal** however if you wish to use **hexadecimal**
please put `#` before the hexadecimal for an example; `#fffb00`

If you think it's too much work **Embed Builder** is also has built in **Color Variables**
this is how it's done (the color variables are limited);
`description:"THE DESCRIPTION",color:{RED}`


**SEE LIST OF AVAILABLE VARIABLES**
**Command:** `embed color`
actions.name: Set Embed Description

actions.message:
**Timestamp**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}ts:`
`timestamp:{CURRENT_TIME}`

**Title + Description + Timestamp**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}t:,${tempVars("ap")}d:,${tempVars("ap")}ts:`
`title:"THE TITLE",description:"THE DESCRIPTION",timestamp:{CURRENT_TIME}`

for timestamp you could just use `{CURRENT_TIME}` variable to make things easier



**Add Field**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}f:[{${tempVars("ap")}n:,${tempVars("ap")}v:}]`
`fields:[{name:"THE TITLE",value:"THE DESCRIPTION"}]`

**Add Field 2**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}f:[{${tempVars("ap")}n:,${tempVars("ap")}v:}],[{${tempVars("ap")}n:,${tempVars("ap")}v:}]`
`fields:[{name:"THE TITLE",value:"THE DESCRIPTION"},{name:"THE TITLE 2",value:"THE DESCRIPTION 2"}]`

**Add Field (InLine)**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}f:[{${tempVars("ap")}n:,${tempVars("ap")}v:,${tempVars("ap")}il:}],[{${tempVars("ap")}n:,${tempVars("ap")}v:,${tempVars("ap")}il:}]`
`fields:[{name:"THE TITLE",value:"THE DESCRIPTION",inline:true},{name:"THE TITLE 2",value:"THE DESCRIPTION 2",inline: true}]`

you can add embed fields up to **25** fields
use `inline:true` to show them inline
actions.name: Set Embed Description

actions.message:
**Image**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}i:`
`image:{url:"https://image.com/IMAGE.png"}`
_or_
`image:"https://image.com/IMAGE.png"`

**Thumbnail**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}th:/${tempVars("ap")}tn:`
`thumbnail:{url:"https://image.com/IMAGE.png"}`
_or_
`thumbnail:"https://image.com/IMAGE.png"`

**Footer**
_aliases:_ `${tempVars("ap")}ft:{${tempVars("ap")}txt:,${tempVars("ap")}iu:}`
`footer:{text:"THE TEXT",icon_url:"https://image.com/IMAGE.png"}`

You can use `\\n` to create new line;
`description:"Line 1 \\nLine 2"`

You can use `\\"` to insert double quote;
`description:"text \\"TEXT \\" text"`


**if you wish to see a few example of how to do multiple format;**
**Command:** `embed example`


I'm sorry i couldn't include all the documentary into **Embed Builder**
Help section, i'm trying my best to make a simple guide for beginner.
However if you wish to learn more about **Discord.js Embeds** You could go to this site;
[Docs](https://discordjs.guide/popular-topics/embeds.html)

-_GrenDy#2045_

actions.message:
**List Of Variables**

You could use these **Variables** inside the json _title, description, footer, etc._
(**CASE SENSITIVE** upperCase Characters, Please write all variables in upperCase)

**USER**
`{USER}` - User Name
`{@USER}` - Mention User
`{USER.ID}` - User ID
`{USER.NICK}` - User Nickname
`{USER.TAG}` - User Tag (user#0000)
`{USER.AVATAR}` - User Avatar URL
`{USER.GAME}` - User Game
`{USER.CUSTOMSTATUS}` - User Custom Status

**SERVER**
`{SERVER}` - Server Name
`{SERVER.ID}` - Server ID
`{SERVER.ICON}` - Server Icon
`{SERVER.OWNER}` - Server Owner Name
`{SERVER.MEMBER.COUNT}` - Server Member Size
`{SERVER.ROLES.COUNT}` - Server Roles Size
`{SERVER.CHANNELS.COUNT}` - Server Channels Size
`{SERVER.BOTS.COUNT}` - Server Bots Size
`{SERVER.CREATEDAT}` - Server Created Date
`{SERVER.ROLE.LIST}` - Server Role List
`{SERVER.CHANNEL.LIST}` - Server Channel List


**CHANNEL**
`{CHANNEL}` - Channel Name
`{#CHANNEL}` - Mention Channel
`{CHANNEL.ID}` - Channel ID
`{CHANNEL.TOPIC}` - Channel Topic

**TIMESTAMP**
`{CURRENT_TIME}` - Current Time in Timestamp 


`{EVERYONE}` - Mention ``@everyone``
`{HERE}` - Mention ``@here``
`<{@}userid>` Tag Specific User (Change userid with id of the member)

``@everyone`` and ``@here`` is not going to work in **Embed**


`{RANDOM_PERCENTAGE}` - Random Percentage 0 - 100%
`{RANDOM_QUOTE}` - Random Quotes
actions.name: Set Embed Description

`embed help 3` for more information

actions.message:
***Commands that can be used to adjust a user's bank account***
/configbank @mentionuser removedebt - Remove all debt and remove all flags from user
/configbank @mentionuser addbankmoney (amount) - Give a user an entered ammount.
/configbank @mentionuser rembankmoney (amount) - Remove an entered ammount from the user

actions.message:
***Admin Commands that can be used to control a user's wallet***
/configbank @mentionuser ratingadd (amount) - Add a given wallet rating amount to user. (Cap at 100 and lowest 0)
/configbank @mentionuser ratingrem (amount) - Remove's a given wallet rating amount to user.
/configbank @mentionuser addmoney (amount) - Give a user an entered ammount.
/configbank @mentionuser remmoney (amount) - Remove an entered ammount from the user
